 {'action': 'created', 'author': 'stoikerty', 'comment_id': 324891142.0, 'datetime': '2017-08-25 11:19:00+00:00', 'masked_author': 'username_2', 'text': "Our team is in the process of migrating our small-but-growing app from sass to glamorous (it's been awesome so far!) and we've come across an issue where we need to style a child component based on the hover of a parent component. It sounds a lot like what you guys are talking about here.

This is the snippet of the original sass-implementation:
```scss
.carousel-item {
  z-index: 1;
